-- Most Asian Stocks Rise on Australia Mining Tax Deal; Commodity Shares Gain
-- Kotaro Tsunetomi
-- 2010-07-02T00:12:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/most-asian-stocks-rise-on-australia-mining-tax-deal-commodity-shares-gain.html

          
          
             Most Asian  stocks  gained, led by
commodity producers, after Australia’s government reached an
agreement with mining companies on a resources tax. Japanese
automakers declined.  
 The MSCI Asia Pacific Index increased 0.1 percent to 112.06
as of 9:08 a.m. in Tokyo. Australia’s S&P/ASX 200 Index rose 0.7
percent. Japan’s Nikkei 225 Stock Average increased 0.4 percent.  
